Utilities for Pandas

Set of utility functions for working with Image data and pandas

{% raw %}

folder2df[source]

folder2df(folder:str, extension:list=None, shuffle:bool=False)

parses all the images in a folder into a pandas dataframe.

{% endraw %} {% raw %}
{% endraw %}

The folder stucture must be as follows -

folder
|- class1
| |- image1
| |- image2
| |- image3
...
|- class2
| |- image1
| |- image2
| |- image3
|- class2
| |- image1
| |- image2
| |- image3
...
...

the classes in the folder will be given as targets and path of image will be stored in image_id

{% raw %}

stratify_df[source]

stratify_df(df:DataFrame, y:str=None, fold_col:str=None, shuffle:bool=False, n_splits=5, random_state=None)

makes stratified folds in df. The Id of the OOF Validation fold will be inserted in fold_col. y is the name of the column to the dependent variable.
